<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,829,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Li" box="[663,770,1333,1358]" pageId="14" pageNumber="365" refString="Li, Z. Z. (1990) Four new species of the genus Scaphoideus (Homoptera: Euscelidae). Acta Zootaxonomia Sinica, 15 (4), 464 - 470. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1990">Li (1990)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[837,927,1333,1358]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
based on seven male specimens. It externally resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[270,584,1369,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculatus">
<emphasis box="[270,584,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="365">Scaphoideus albomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be readily distinguished by the narrowed connective processes and aedeagus with a pair of apical lateral processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
